label: CcBrR
comment: Finds a Base Station connected to a backhaul Core Network and providing a RAN, both of which are part of a Cellular Network.

label: CNCN
comment: Finds a Cellular Network implemented by a Core Network.

label: CNHS
comment: Finds a core network implementing a cellular network accessible from a space in which there is a device connected to but not providing the cellular network.

label: CNR
comment: Finds a cellular network provided by a router.

label: CN-R
comment: Finds a cellular network that is not provided by a router.

label: CrCcL3
comment: Finds a core router providing a core network backhaul for a cellular network, connected to an IP subnet that is not part of the cellular network.

label: CScGcCS
comment: Finds a Physical Host connected between two distinct Cellular networks, both in the same space.

label: FCNS
comment: Finds a Cellular Network to which is connected a Fixed Host (or a Virtual Host running on it) located in a Space.

label: L3cCrC
comment: Finds a core router providing a core network backhaul for a cellular network, connected to an IP subnet that is not part of the cellular network.

label: MPCNS
comment: Finds a Public Cellular Network to which is connected a Mobile Host (or a Virtual Host running on it) located in a Space.

label: PcCN
comment: Finds a process controlling a cellular network and an associated RAN.

label: PCN
comment: Finds a Public Cellular Network.

label: PCNRWI
comment: Finds router providing a Public Cellular Network accessible from the World, along with the Internet which should also be accessible from the World.

label: RrBcC
comment: Finds a BaseStation providing a RAN and connected to a core network both of which are part of a cellular network.

label: CP
comment: Finds a solo Control Process.

label: D
comment: Finds a solo Data asset that is not unsolicited email.

label: HE-Hu
comment: Finds a host running an Editor that doesn't have a user.

label: HHuWE
comment: Finds a Human using both an email client and a web browser on the same host.

label: HHuWSMS
comment: Finds a Human using both an SMS client and a web browser on the same host.

label: HIP-Hu
comment: Finds a host running an interactive process that doesn't have a user.

label: HuaDirPaD-P
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that amends Data, where the Human amends that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data.

label: HuaD-P
comment: Finds a Human entering but not viewing Data, where the Data is not Spam, and there is no interactive process mediating the interaction.

label: HuHWES
comment: Finds a Human using a web browser running on a host to access email.

label: HuiCHDtS-AC
comment: Finds a human interacting with a console host and a desktop service running on a remote host, where the user does not interact with a desktop client that uses the desktop service.

label: HuiDirIPpD-P
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Interactive Process that processes Data, where the Human enters that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data.

label: HuiDirPpD-P
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes Data, where the Human enters that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data.

label: HuiPiDCHS
comment: Finds a user interacting directly with a process to enter data using a console host located in a space.

label: HuiRACHSPiD
comment: Finds a user entering data via remote interaction with a process using a remote access client on a console host located in a space.

label: HuirEaD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Editor that amends Data.

label: HuirEc-rD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Editor that creates but does not receive Data.

label: HuirEp-iD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Editor that processes Data, where the Human does not enter that Data.

label: HuirIPaD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with an Interactive Process that amends data.

label: HuirIPp-iD
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Interactive Process that processes Data, where the Human does not enter the Data.

label: HuirIPp-xD
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with an Interactive Process that processes Data, where the Human does not interact with the Data.

label: HuirPaD+eUI-O
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a process that amends (creates and receives) data, and enables user input but not output of the data.

label: HuirPc-iD-rC-vHu-DS
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a process that creates data, where the data is not stored on any host, used by any process nor viewed by any user, and the Human does not enter the Data.

label: HuirPr-iD-cD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with a Process that receives Data, but does not create any output, and the Human does not enter the Data.

label: HuirPr-vD-cC-iHu-DS
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely with a Process that receives Data that is not viewed by the Human, and which is not created by any process, stored on any Host, nor input by any Human.

label: HuirPsD
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a process that serves data. This conflicts with domain model assumptions.

label: Hui-vD-P
comment: Finds a Human entering but not viewing Data, where the Data is not Spam, and there is no interactive process mediating the interaction.

label: HuRACuPD
comment: Finds Human interacting remotely via a remote access client with a process that processes data.

label: HuRDRASPH
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Desktop with a Process that is not a Remote Access Service, and a collocated Remote Access Service.

label: HuRDuPH-DtS
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Desktop client with a Process that is not a remote access service, running on a Host that lacks a Desktop Service used by the same Human, and where the Remote Desktop is the last remote access client in the chain between the Human and the Process.

label: HuRTRASCPH
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Terminal with a Console Process that is not a Remote Access Service, and a collocated Remote Access Service.

label: HuRTuCPH-LnS
comment: Finds a Human interacting via a Remote Terminal client with a Process that is not a remote access service, running on a Host that lacks a Login Service used by the same Human.

label: HuvDirPcD-P
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that creates Data, where the Human views that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data.

label: HuvDirPrD-P
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that receives Data, where the Human views that Data, but no process is yet enabling the interaction with the data.

label: Huv-iD-P
comment: Finds a Human viewing but not entering Data, where the Data is not Spam, and there is no interactive process mediating the interaction.

label: HuWES
comment: Finds a Human using a web browser to access email.

label: PpD+noDU
comment: Finds a Process that is processing Data, where the Process has a self-referential noDU link indicating it should not be processing data.

label: RDuDtS
comment: Finds a remote desktop client using a desktop service.

label: RDuDtSuPH
comment: Finds a remote desktop service using a process on the same host, and used by a remote desktop client.

label: RDuP-LnS
comment: Finds a remote desktop client using a process that is not a login service.

label: RDuRDuS-uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop using remotely another remote desktop which is using remotely a third process that is not yet remotely used by the first.

label: RDuRTuS-uR
comment: Finds a remote desktop using remotely a remote terminal which is using remotely a third process that is not yet remotely used by the first.

label: RTuCP
comment: Finds a remote terminal client using a console-accessible process.

label: RTuRASuCPH
comment: Finds a remote access service using a console process on the same host, and used by a remote terminal client.

label: Ct
comment: Finds a solo Container.

label: CtDS
comment: Finds a Container that stores a copy of Data (which is actually not allowed).

label: CtHaH
comment: Finds a Container provisioned by a Host that is above another Host.

label: CtHhPH
comment: Finds a Container provisioned by a Host that has a PhysicalHost.

label: CtH-iP
comment: Finds a container provisioned by a Host that is not a Pod.

label: DCCM-A
comment: Finds a Data Centre with a Cluster on which is provisioned a Pod management Master node that does not yet host an API Server.

label: DCCMCAP
comment: Finds a process controlling a data centre hosting a K8s master node running a K8s API server and Ingress proxy.

label: DCCM-P
comment: Finds a Data Centre with a Cluster on which is provisioned a Pod management Master node that does not yet host an Ingress reverse proxy.

label: DCCt-Pod
comment: Finds a Container managed directly by a Data Centre and not via a Pod.

label: DCMW-LS
comment: Finds a K8s Master and Worker on the same (cluster) Host in a Data Centre, where the Master and Worker are not on any common subnet.

label: DCPHM
comment: Finds a K8s Master whose physical host is in a Data Centre.

label: DCPHW
comment: Finds a K8s Worker whose physical host is in a Data Centre.

label: DCPS-Pod
comment: Finds a Process hosted directly on a Data Centre, but not contained by a Pod managed by the Data Centre.

label: DCVHC
comment: Finds a DataCentre containing a Cluster, and a Virtual Host.managed by the Data Centre rather than being provisioned on a Host.

label: HCt
comment: Finds a host provisioned by a container.

label: Hum-iH-AC
comment: Finds a human remotely managing a host but lacking a suitable connection to its management service.

label: Hum-iHRAS
comment: Finds a human managing but not interacting with a host that is not a Pod and has a root privileged remote access service.

label: Hum-iSH-LnS
comment: Finds a Human managing but not interacting with a Shell Host, where there is no process controlling the host.

label: HumPC-Hu
comment: Finds an unmanaged Container of a Process managed by a Human.

label: KIP-S
comment: Finds an Ingress proxy mediating access to a service, but not controlled by any other process.

label: KPxCaSI
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting an unprivileged service in a Container, accessed for authentication purposes by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPxCLnSA
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting a remote access service running in and controlling a Container, and used by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPxCuScP
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting an unprivileged service in a Container, which controls another service accessed by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPxCuSI
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting an unprivileged service in a Container, accessed by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPxMLnSA
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Master node that runs a K8s API Server, connected via a Subnet to a K8s Worker cluster, and used by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPxWLnSA
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Worker node, connected via a Subnet to a Master that runs a K8s API Server, and used by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPyCLnSA
comment: Finds a Pod managed by K8S or equivalent, hosting a remote access service running in and controlling a Container, and used for authentication by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPyMLnSA
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Master node that runs a K8s API Server, connected via a Subnet to a K8s Worker cluster, and used for authentication by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: KPyWLnSA
comment: Finds a Remote Access Service that runs on and controls a K8s Worker node, connected via a Subnet to a Master that runs a K8s API Server, and used for authentication by a client from outside the K8S cluster.

label: MWHLS
comment: Finds K8s Master and Worker nodes on the same (cluster) host, and connected to the same subnet.

label: MWPodLS2
comment: Finds a Pod running on a K8s Worker connected via a Logical Subnet to a K8s Master, which can also access an overlay on the Logical Subnet.

label: Pc-hSHLnS
comment: Finds a Process controlling a Shell Host that runs a Remote Access Service, but the Shell Host is not a Pod and not the Process host.

label: PodCnD
comment: Finds Data stored on a Container provisioned by a Pod.

label: PodCnP
comment: Finds a Process hosted by a Container provisioned by a Pod.

label: PodCnPD
comment: Finds a Container running a Process that handles Data stored on the associated Pod.

label: PodDCC-M
comment: Finds a Pod managed by a Data Centre that has a Cluster, but there is no Master node provisioned on the Cluster.

label: PodDCMC-W-H
comment: Finds a K8s Pod with no Host managed by a Data Centre that has a Cluster with a K8s Master, where the Data Centre does not yet have a K8s Worker cluster.

label: PodHaH
comment: Finds a Pod provisioned by a Host that is above another Host.

label: PodHhPH
comment: Finds a Pod provisioned by a Host that has a PhysicalHost.

label: PodMP
comment: Finds a solo Pod.

label: PodP-Cn
comment: Finds a Pod containing a Process but with no intervening Container.

label: SHVH
comment: Finds a Virtual Host provisioned on a Simple Host that is not a Pod.

label: VH-LnS
comment: Finds a Virtual Host that is not controlled by any process.

label: CSDFdDA2
comment: Finds a process participating in a data flow fulfilled by another process.

label: D+DS-cP-iHu
comment: Finds a Data asset that is not email and is not created by any process or user input, but is stored on at least one host. Such Data would need to be static for this situation to make sense.

label: DADS
comment: Finds a Data Access fulfilling a Data Copy.

label: DADU-eS
comment: Finds a service controlling access to a data access, which fulfils a data use that is not yet controlled by any process.

label: DAllDS
comment: Finds all stored copies of a Data asset.

label: DBsDP
comment: Finds a DB process that is serving data, and the associated Data Access object.

label: DBsDRDF
comment: Finds a DB serving data that is stored on a separate Host and supplied to the DB in a data flow.

label: DBsDRSDS
comment: Finds a DB serving data that is stored on a separate Host and served to the DB by a Process there.

label: DCPDF
comment: Finds a cache Data Copy on a Host fulfilling a Data Flow (excluding Spam) between source and destination processes, plus optionally the users responsible for the two processes.

label: D-DS-cP-iHu
comment: Finds a Data asset that is not email and is not created by any process or user input, and not stored on any host. Such Data is neither dynamic nor static, and since it must be one or the other, it must be an error.

label: DSDA
comment: Finds a Data Access fulfilled by a Data Copy.

label: DUDA-eS
comment: Finds a service controlling access to a data access, which is fulfilled by a data use that is not yet controlled by any process.

label: HD-aHD-DS
comment: Finds a Host that stores Data but has no Data Copy yet, and is not in a virtualisation stack above another Host that stores the same data.

label: HDBDRDF
comment: Finds a Host running a DB process acting as a Data Relay for a Data Flow to a destination process, and optionally the DB Process and Host managers.

label: HDBDSDF
comment: Finds a Host running a DB process acting as a Stored Data Pool for a Data Flow to a destination process, and optionally the DB Process and Host managers.

label: HDBsD
comment: Finds a Host of a Database that is serving locally stored Data.

label: HDS
comment: Finds a stored copy of Data on a Host, and its Physical Host.

label: HPDAcDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD creates locally stored Data, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDAdDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD deletes locally stored Data, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDADF
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that sends a Data Flow to a destination process, plus the associated Data and Data Access assets, and optionally the Process and Host managers.

label: HPDAd-pDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD deletes locally stored Data served not processed by the Process, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDADS2dDO
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that writes to a local stored Data Copy, and sources data from two distinct data producers.

label: HPDADS-crudu
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy fulfilled by a local process that does not CRUD update the data copy.

label: HPDADSDU
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy fulfilled by a Data Access that sources data from a Data Update (from a process on any Host).

label: HPDAuDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD updates locally stored Data, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDDR+DS+DFfi-fiDF
comment: Finds Host running a Process relaying Data which is stored somewhere in the system, where Data flows to the relay from a data store, but is not sent from the relay.

label: HPDDR+DS-DA2
comment: Finds Host running a Process relaying Data which is stored somewhere in the system, where there is no flow of data through the relay.

label: HPDDR+DS-DFfo+foDF
comment: Finds Host running a Process relaying Data which is stored in the system, where Data flows from the relay to a data store, but is not received from any data producer.

label: HPDDR-DS+DFfi-fiDF
comment: Finds Host running a Process relaying Data which is not stored in the system, where Data flows to the relay from a data producer, but is not sent from the relay.

label: HPDDR-DS-DA2
comment: Finds Host running a Process relaying Data which is not stored in the system, where there is no flow of data through the relay.

label: HPDFDADS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that receives an incoming Data Flow and writes the data to local storage, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDFDAuDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD updates locally stored Data by saving an incoming Data Flow, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDFDI
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that receives an incoming Data Flow and uses it as input, plus optionally the host and process managers. The Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: HPDOcDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD creates locally stored Data which it produces as output, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDOdDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD deletes locally stored Data which it produces as output, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDODF
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that creates (possibly from user input) a Data Flow to a destination process, plus the associated Data and Data Output assets, and optionally the Process and Host managers.

label: HPDOuDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD updates locally stored Data which it produces as output, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPDSCDF
comment: Finds a Process sending an output data flow that is cached, and optionally the process host manager.

label: HPDSDA-crudr
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy that fulfils a Data Access by a Process on the same Host, where there is no CRUDR relationship between the Process and Data Copy.

label: HPDSDADF
comment: Finds a Host storing a Data Copy that is read and sent in a data flow by a Process on the same Host, plus optionally the Host and Process managers.

label: HPDS-fDI-DO-DFI
comment: Finds a Host with a stored Data Copy, running a Process that has a Data Input asset for the same Data that is not yet fulfilled by the stored Data Copy, which is also not fulfilled by an incoming data flow, and where the process does not have a Data Output asset (i.e. the Data Access is not a Data Update).

label: HPDSrDI
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD reads a locally stored copy of Data it uses as input, plus optionally the Host and Process managers.

label: HPDSr-pDA
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD reads a locally stored copy of Data it serves but does not process, plus optionally the Host and Process managers.

label: HPeD
comment: Finds a Host for a Process that creates and appends to locally stored Data.

label: HP-iDOdDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that has the right to delete locally stored Data which it computes as output (i.e. not coming from a user), plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HP-iDODF
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that creates (not from user input) a Data Flow to a destination process, plus the associated Data and Data Output assets, and optionally the Process and Host managers.

label: HP-iDS
comment: Finds a Host running a process that stores a local copy of data that it did not get from a user, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HP-iDSDI
comment: Finds a stored data input to a process, which is not reviewed and updated by a user, plus the process and data host and optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPmDFDAcDS
comment: Finds a Host running a Process that CRUD creates locally stored Data from one or more incoming flows, plus optionally the host and process managers.

label: HPsD-DS
comment: Finds a Process serving (but not processing) Data and the process host, where there is no copy of the data stored on the same host.

label: HPsDPDFDS
comment: Finds a Host that stores a copy of Data served by and sent to a Process on the same Host, plus the associated Data Flow and Data Pool.

label: HPsDPDSDF
comment: Finds a Host that stores a copy of Data served by and sent from a Process on the same Host, plus the associated Data Flow and Data Pool.

label: HPuDSDI
comment: Finds a stored data input needed by a process, plus the process and data host and optionally the host and process managers.

label: HP-uDSDI
comment: Finds a stored data input to a process, which does not depend on the data, plus the process and data host and optionally the host and process managers.

label: HuaD-DS
comment: Finds a Human that alters (views and inputs) data where there is not yet a DataCopy relating to the data.

label: HuaDPH-DS-DA
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, and as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data.

label: HuaDPH-DS-DP
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, and as yet no Data Pool anywhere associated with this Data.

label: HuaDRAC-DA
comment: Finds a Human amending Data remotely via a Remote Access Client, where there is no Data Access asset for access to the Data by the RAC.

label: HuaDSPH-DP
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the data.

label: HuiPv-iDFCHS
comment: Finds a user interacting directly with a process to view but not enter data using a console host located in a space, where the data comes from an inbound data flow.

label: HuiPv-iD-FCHS
comment: Finds a user interacting directly with a process to view but not enter data using a console host located in a space, where the data does not comes from a data flow.

label: HuiRACv-iDFCHS
comment: Finds a user interacting directly with a process to view data using a remote access client on a console host located in a space.

label: HuirPD
comment: Finds a Human interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that is using Data.

label: HuirPiD-DF-DS
comment: Finds Human interacting (possibly remotely) with and entering Data via a Process, which does not just store or forward the data.

label: HuirPiDF
comment: Finds a (possibly remote) user of an interactive process that enters data sent from the process in a data flow.

label: HuirPiDS
comment: Finds a (possibly remote) user of an interactive process that inputs data stored from the process in a local data copy.

label: HuirPvDF
comment: Finds a (possibly remote) user of an interactive process that views data received by the process in a data flow.

label: HuirPvDS
comment: Finds a (possibly remote) user of an interactive process that views data loaded by the process from a local data copy.

label: HuirPv-iD
comment: Finds a (possibly remote) user of an interactive process that views but does not update data created by the process.

label: Hui-vDPH-DS-DA
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, and there is as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data.

label: Hui-vDPH-DS-DP
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is no copy on the same Host, where there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the data.

label: Hui-vDSPH-DP
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the data.

label: HuWEDF
comment: Finds a Human using a web browser that is receiving a data flow from an email service.

label: HuWESDF
comment: Finds a Human using a web browser to access email, including URLs contained in emails.

label: HuWSMSDF
comment: Finds a Human using a web browser and an SMS client on the same host, accessing URLs from SMS messages via the browser.

label: PaD-DS
comment: Finds a process that alters (read and write) output data where there is not yet a DataCopy relating to the data.

label: PaDH-DS-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data.

label: PaDH-DS-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the Process is not enabling a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data pool anywhere associated with this Data.

label: PaDSH-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the Process is not enabling a user to amend the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data.

label: PcPr-uDS
comment: Finds two distinct processes accessing the same stored copy of data, one of which receives the data (processes it as an input) but does not depend on it.

label: PcPuDS
comment: Finds two distinct processes accessing the same stored copy of data, one of which reads the data (processes it as a necessary input).

label: Pc-rDH-DS-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data.

label: Pc-rDH-DS-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data.

label: Pc-rDSH-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the Process is not enabling a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data.

label: PDF
comment: Finds a Data Flow (excluding Spam), plus source and destination processes, plus optionally the users responsible for the two processes. The destination process is matched twice so it can be referred to in either role.

label: PDFIDADFI
comment: Finds a Process that receives a flow of Data from a data store or source that it does not get from local storage, and forwards it towards a data consumer. The Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: PDFODADFO
comment: Finds a Process that receives a flow of Data from a data producer that it does not get from local storage, and forwards it towards a data store. The Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: PDI
comment: Finds a Process that uses Data as input, or displays it to an interactive user.

label: PDI+DO-DS-S
comment: Finds a Process that uses Data as input, or displays it to an interactive user, where the data is not stored anywhere, and there is no process that enables and controls the Data access, but there is a process creating the data.

label: PDI+DS-S
comment: Finds a Process that uses Data as input, or displays it to an interactive user, where there is at least one stored copy of the data, but there is no process that enables and controls the Data access.

label: PDI-Hu
comment: Finds a Process that uses Data as input and does not have an interactive user.

label: PDO
comment: Finds a Process that creates Data as output, or gets it from an interactive user.

label: PDO+DS-S
comment: Finds a Process that creates Data as output, or gets it from an interactive user, where there is at least one stored copy of the data, but there is no process that enables and controls access.

label: PDR
comment: Finds a Process acting as a Data Relay.

label: PHHD
comment: Finds a Physical Host, plus data stored on the host or on a virtual host running on the physical host.

label: PHHDS
comment: Finds a Physical Host located in a Space, plus data stored on the host or on a virtual host running there, plus optionally a user of the physical host.

label: P-iDFDI
comment: Finds a data flow to a process that uses the data as input, where the data does not come from an interactive user, plus optionally the process manager.  The Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: PmDFIDADFI
comment: Finds a Process that forwards flowing data from one or more sources but not from local storage in the direction of a data consumer, plus the associated Data and Data Access assets. The forwarding Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: PmDFODADFO
comment: Finds a Process that forwards flowing data from one or more sources but not from local storage in the direction of a data store or source, plus the associated Data and Data Access assets. The forwarding Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: PpDP
comment: Finds a host running a process that is processing data.

label: Pr-cDH-DS-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is no copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data.

label: Pr-cDSH-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no Data Pool associated with the Data.

label: PSDP
comment: Finds a Process that serves stored Data.

label: PsDSH-DP
comment: Finds a Process serving (but not processing) Data stored on its own local Host, and the corresponding Data Copy, where there is no data pool associated with the same data.

label: PuDFDI
comment: Finds a data flow to a process that needs the data as input, plus optionally the process manager.

label: P-uDFDI
comment: Finds a data flow to a process that uses the data as input without depending on the data, plus optionally the process manager. The Process is matched twice, so it can be referred to by either role name.

label: RUIDO
comment: Finds a Process that enables remote user input.

label: RUODI
comment: Finds a Process that enables remote user output.

label: S2dC2dDX
comment: Finds a process with two distinct clients, each providing a different input, one of which is not stored on the process host.

label: SDUDADS
comment: Finds a Service enabling access for a Data Use, where the Service writes to a local Data Copy.

label: SDUDSDA
comment: Finds a Service enabling access for a Data Use, where the Service reads from a local Data Copy.

label: StoPDA
comment: Finds a Stakeholder operating a Process that accesses Data.

label: DADC2DP2S+fwd-ch
comment: Finds a Process with a Data Access having a Data Channel to a Service where data flows forwards along the channel, using a Data Path that extends a second Data Path used by a second Data Channel for the same Data Access, that isn't yet to the Service.

label: DADC2DP2S+rev-ch
comment: Finds a Process with a Data Access having a Data Channel to a Service where data flows backwards along the channel, using a Data Path that extends a second Data Path used by a second Data Channel for the same Data Access, that isn't yet to the Service.

label: DADSDCSDD-f
comment: Finds a data access process that acts as a data source and itself gets the data from an original source, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data destination that does not receive data from this original source.

label: DC3-x
comment: Finds a Data Channel extending a second Data Channel which extends a third Data Channel, where the first does not yet extend the third.

label: DDDCDP2oDS
comment: Finds a Data Desination for which there is an untried Data Channel to a next Process, which uses a Data Path that extends another Data Path to another Process, and where no previously found process is a data source.

label: DDDCDS2P
comment: Finds a Data Channel for a Data Destination, where the channel ends at a Data Source, and the Data Channel is tagged by a reverse link from the Data Destination indicating there is a data flow backwards along the channel, plus the associated source and destination Processes and the Data.

label: DDDPS-DC
comment: Finds a Data Path from a Process that is a Data Destination to a Service, where there is no Data Channel using the Data Path.

label: DD-fDCSDS
comment: Finds a data access process that acts as a data destination that is not fulfilled by any other process, and has a data channel to a service that can act as a data source.

label: DFDCI4P
comment: Finds a Data Flow between two processes, fulfilled a reverse flow along a Data Channel between two possibly intermediate processes.

label: DFDCO4P
comment: Finds a Data Flow between two processes, fulfilled a forward flow along a Data Channel between two possibly intermediate processes.

label: DFTPACS
comment: Finds a DataFlow to a Process that can flow when (the process host is) in a Space.

label: DI-fDCSDS
comment: Finds a process using input and acting as a data destination that is not yet fulfilled (sent data) by any process, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data source.

label: DO-fDCSDD
comment: Finds a data output process that acts as a data source but does not itself get the data from any original source, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data destination.

label: DSDCDD2P
comment: Finds a Data Channel for a Data Source, where the channel ends at a Data Destination, and the Data Channel is tagged by a forward link from the Data Source indicating there is a data flow forwards along the channel, plus the associated source and destination Processes and the Data.

label: DSDCDP2oDD
comment: Finds a Data Source for which there is a Data Channel to a next Process, which uses a Data Path that extends another Data Path to another Process, and where no previously found process is a data destination.

label: DSDPS
comment: Finds a data path from a process to a service, where the process is a source of the data.

label: DUDSDCSDD
comment: Finds a data access process that acts as a data source and sends data to a data destination where the original source is a data update.

label: HPDFDI-fDS-DP
comment: Finds a Host with a stored Data Copy, running a Process that has a Data Input asset for the same Data that does not yet fulfil the stored Data Copy, and the Data Input is fulfilled by an incoming Data Flow, but there is no Data Pool for this data and any process on the same Host.

label: HPDXfr-cAC
comment: Finds a host running a process in a context from which data flows but cannot flow in that context, due to limited connectivity, and where the host does not hold a stored copy of the data.

label: HPDXtr-cAC
comment: Finds a host running a process in a context to which data flows but cannot flow in that context, due to limited connectivity, and where the host does not hold a stored copy of the data.

label: HSDADPPDXP-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a non-interactive process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access, where all three processes have the same host.

label: HuaDSPH+S-DA
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is a  Data Pool associated with the data at that Host but as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data.

label: HuaDSPH-S-DA
comment: Finds a Human amending Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is no Data Pool associated with the data at that Host and as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data.

label: Hui-vDSPH+S-DA
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is a Data Pool associated with the data at that Host but as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data.

label: Hui-vDSPH-S-DA
comment: Finds a Human entering Data by interacting (possibly remotely) with a Process that processes the Data, of which there is a copy on the same Host, where there is no Data Pool associated with the data at that Host and as yet no Data Access associated with this Process and Data.

label: PaDSH+S-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, but there is at least one Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data.

label: PaDSH-S-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is amending data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, and no Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data.

label: Pc-rDSH+S-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, but there is at least one Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data.

label: Pc-rDSH-S-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is creating data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, and no Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data.

label: PDP-DP
comment: Finds a Process that implicitly or explicitly serves stored Data, where the Data has no Data Path.

label: Pr-cDSH+S-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, but there is at least one Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data.

label: Pr-cDSH-S-Hu-DA
comment: Finds a Process that is receiving data of which there is a copy stored on the same host, where the process does not enable a user to enter the data, and there is as yet no data access associated with this Process and Data, and no Data Pool at this Host associated with the Data.

label: RA-fDCSDD
comment: Finds a remote access client acting as a data source but not itself getting the data from any original source, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data destination.

label: RA-fDCSDS
comment: Finds a remote access client acting as a data destination that is not fulfilled (sent data) by any process, and having a data channel to a service that can act as a data source.

label: SDADPPDXP-DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access.

label: SDADPPDXP-Hu-DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a non-interactive process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access.

label: SDADPPDXPRAC-DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a process that exchanges data with a third process which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access, and there is a remote access client using remotely the second and third processes.

label: SDADPPDXRAC-DP
comment: Finds a service with a data access to which there is a data path from a process that exchanges data with a remote access client which is not the service and from which there is no data path to the same data access.

label: HuSDPoS-i
comment: Finds a Stakeholder operating a Process that is using Special Category Data relating to a Human data subject, where the subject operates the Service providing (and controlling) access to the data but not the Process using it.

label: HuSDPS-io
comment: Finds a Stakeholder operating a Process that is using Special Category Data relating to a Human data subject who is not operating the process providing access to the data.

label: NDFHuoO
comment: Finds nationally regulated personal data being transferred across a border to a process that optionally has an operator organisation.

label: Co
comment: Finds a solo Controller.

label: CoPD
comment: Finds a Controller with its onboard data and the control process that uses this data to control physical processes.

label: CoPDsFT
comment: Finds a Controller with its onboard data and the control process that uses this data to control physical processes, plus flows of the data to this process, at least one of which must be involved.

label: CoPsDmFF
comment: Finds a Controller with its onboard data and the process that serves the data making it available to external clients, plus all flows of this data from the process (i.e., out of the sensor), all of which must be involved in the pattern.

label: HuiThaS-S
comment: Finds a Human that has access to a space and uses an IoT Thing which has no specified location.

label: HuiUCo
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a UserController, plus onboard data and processing.

label: HuiUSe
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a UserSensor, plus onboard data and processing.

label: HumThP-m
comment: Finds a Human managing a Thing with an unmanaged onboard process.

label: Pa-uCo
comment: Finds a client Process that amends an IoT Controller, along with its onboard  communication Process and Data.

label: PpSe
comment: Finds a Process polling a Sensor, and the onboard Process and Data at the Sensor.

label: Pr-uSe
comment: Finds a client Process that receives data from an IoT Sensor, along with its onboard simple communication Process and Data.

label: PuCo
comment: Finds a client Process that updates an IoT Controller, along with its onboard  communication Process serving onboard Data.

label: PuSe
comment: Finds a client Process that reads data from an IoT Sensor, along with its onboard simple communication Process and Data.

label: Se
comment: Finds a solo Sensor.

label: SePD
comment: Finds a Sensor with its onboard process and data.

label: SePDmFF
comment: Finds a Sensor with its onboard process and data, plus all flows of this data from the process (i.e., out of the sensor), all of which must be involved in the pattern.

label: SePDsFF
comment: Finds a Sensor with its onboard process and data, plus all flows of this data from the process (i.e., out of the sensor), at least one of which must be involved in the pattern.

label: SHuTh-Hu
comment: Finds a Human managing a Space in which an unmanaged Thing is located.

label: DFHuoO
comment: Finds personal data being transferred across a border to a process that optionally has an operator organisation.

label: DSHuoO
comment: Finds personal data being communicated across a border, to a process that is an intermediary (not the final destination) and optionally has an operator organisation.

label: Hu-aDoPS-o
comment: Finds a Service that serves data relating to a Human data subject who may be a child, along with its host and operator, and data processing operated by the subject that uses this Service.

label: HuDoPS-o
comment: Finds a Service that serves data relating to a Human data subject, along with its host and operator, and data processing operated by the subject that uses this Service.

label: HuDP-J
comment: Finds personal data used by a Process that is not controlled by the data subject, and is not subject to a well defined jurisdiction.

label: HuDPoJoSt
comment: Finds a Process using Data relating to a Human who is not the Process operator, plus optionally the process Operator and Jurisdication.

label: HuDP-St
comment: Finds a Process that is using Data relating to a Human data subject, but there is no data controller defined.

label: HuDSH-J
comment: Finds a Host for which there is no Jurisdiction that is storing Data related to a Human who is not the operator of the Host.

label: HuDSHoJoSt
comment: Finds a Host that is storing Data relating to a Human data subject who is not the Host operator, plus optionally the actual Operator and the Jurisdiction for the Host.

label: HuDSH-St
comment: Finds a Host storing Data related to a Human, where the host is not operated by the human, and it has no data controller.

label: JuHP
comment: Finds a host subject to a jurisdiction that is hosting a process.

label: JuPHS
comment: Finds a host that is or runs on a physical host located in a space subject to a jurisdiction.

label: JuSS
comment: Finds space subject to a jurisdiction which is the entrance to another space that has no jurisdiction.

label: BPcGcBP
comment: Finds a Bluetooth device paired with two other devices.

label: HBImSG
comment: Finds a pair of hosts pairing via Bluetooth, and the spaces in which the pair operates.

label: HBISG
comment: Finds a pair of hosts pairing via Bluetooth in a Space.

label: HBTTHS-S
comment: Finds a Host in a Space that accepts pairing via Bluetooth with a TrivialHost that has no location.

label: HL1H
comment: Finds two hosts connected via a Bluetooth or USB pair, and the space in which this connection is established, the interface connecting with one of them, and optionally the manager of that host.

label: HL1HS
comment: Finds two distinct hosts in a space connected via a Bluetooth or USB pair, the associated location access contexts, and optionally the manager of the local host.

label: HpBRH
comment: Finds two Physical Hosts that are paired over Bluetooth.

label: HpURH
comment: Finds two Physical Hosts that are paired over USB.

label: HuiHBTTH-Hu
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via Bluetooth with another host used by a Human.

label: HuiHUSBTH-Hu
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via USB with another host used by a Human.

label: HUISG
comment: Finds a pair of hosts pairing via USB, and the space in which they are located.

label: HumHBTTH-Hu
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via Bluetooth with another host managed by a Human.

label: HumHUSBTH-Hu
comment: Finds a TrivialHost with no manager, paired via USB with another host managed by a Human.

label: HumTHS
comment: Finds a Human managing a Trivial Host located in a space.

label: HUSBTHS-S
comment: Finds a Host in a Space that accepts pairing via USB with a TrivialHost that has no location.

label: L13SSg2
comment: Finds a gateway from a layer 1 subnet (i.e. Bluetooth or USB connection) via a gateway to an IP subnet, along with the forward and return path segments via the gateway.

label: L13SSg2AC
comment: Finds a gateway from a layer 1 subnet (i.e. Bluetooth or USB connection) via a gateway to an IP subnet, along with the forward and return path segments via the gateway, and a context in which the gateway is connected to both subnets.

label: L1c-rGcL3
comment: Finds a physical host with a pairing connection from a distinct host that is also connected to an IP subnet, all in the same space. This is a PC on a network that has a link to a USB or Bluetooth device.

label: L1rGcL3
comment: Finds a Bluetooth or USB device connected from a host to an IP subnet, all in the same space.

label: L1SSg2
comment: Finds a gateway between two distinct layer 1 subnets (i.e. Bluetooth or USB connections), along with the forward and return path segments via the gateway.

label: L1SSg2AC
comment: Finds a gateway between two distinct layer 1 subnets (i.e. Bluetooth or USB connections), along with the forward and return path segments via the gateway, and a context in which the gateway is connected to both subnets.

label: L31SSg2
comment: Finds a gateway from an IP subnet via a gateway to a layer 1 subnet (i.e. Bluetooth or USB connection), along with the forward and return path segments via the gateway.

label: L31SSg2AC
comment: Finds a gateway from an IP subnet via a gateway to a layer 1 subnet (i.e. Bluetooth or USB connection), along with the forward and return path segments via the gateway, and a context in which the gateway is connected to both subnets.

label: L3cGc-rL1
comment: Finds a Physical Host gateway on an IP subnet with a paring connection from a USB or Bluetooth device, all in the same space.

label: L3cGrL1
comment: Finds a USB/Bluetooth device connected from an IP subnet to a Host, all in the same space.

label: UHDpP-S
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB Device paired with a USB Host which is running a process using the Data, and the Data is not also stored on the USB Host.

label: UHDrP-S
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB Device paired with a USB Host that does not also store the data, where the data is used by a Process running on a third distinct host.

label: UHDSrP
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB Device paired with a USB Host running a service for the Data, where the data is used by a Process running on some other host that doesn't use any other process capable of providing the data.

label: UHS
comment: Finds a USB Host located in a Space.

label: UPc-rGrUP
comment: Finds a USB hub between a USB device and a USB host (it provides the USB Pair from the USB Host, but not to the USB device).

label: UPrGc-rUP
comment: Finds a USB hub between a USB host and a USB device (it provides the USB Pair from the USB Host, but not to the USB device).

label: USBD-S
comment: Finds Data stored on a USB device where there is no local process serving the data or creating it from scratch.

label: AC
comment: Finds a solo AuthClient.

label: AS
comment: Finds a solo authentication/authorisation service.

label: C
comment: Finds a Host that represents a virtual or physical cluster.

label: CcuS
comment: Finds a client accessing and controlling a service (which should never happen).

label: CH
comment: Finds a solo Fixed Console Host.

label: CHS
comment: Finds a Console Host located in a Space, with associated access contexts and optionally an interactive user and system manager.

label: CHS-iP
comment: Finds a Console Host located in a Space, with associated access contexts and optionally an interactive user and system manager, where the device is not a personal device.

label: CuSHS
comment: Finds a Host that is not a Cluster running both a Client and a Service used by the Client, in a Space.

label: DC
comment: Finds a solo Data Centre.

label: DC-C
comment: Finds a Data Centre with no server cluster of its own.

label: DCH
comment: Finds a Physical Host resourced by a Data Centre.

label: DCLS
comment: Finds a DataCentre connected to an Abstract Subnet, and a Router located in the DataCentre.

label: DCpLS
comment: Finds a DataCentre providing a LogicalSubnet.

label: DC-R
comment: Finds a Data Centre without its own Router.

label: DCVHRS-H
comment: Finds a Host that is physically in a DataCentre and connected to a WiFi LAN that is not provided by any host.

label: DCVHWS-H
comment: Finds a Host that is physically in a DataCentre and connected to a Wired LAN that is not provided by any host.

label: DCWH-LS
comment: Finds a Data Centre with a router and wired network, in which is located another Fixed Host not connected to or providing any subnet.

label: FcLSS
comment: Finds a Logical Subnet to which is connected a Fixed Host (or a Virtual Host running on it) located in a Space.

label: FpLSS
comment: Finds a Logical Subnet which is provided by a Fixed Host (or a Virtual Host running on it) located in a Space.

label: GH
comment: Finds a General Host (i.e. a host that can run arbitrary processes).

label: H
comment: Finds a solo Host, with optionally its manager(s) and interactive user(s).

label: HAC
comment: Finds a Host in a Space with the associated access context, with optionally its manager, and all related access contexts.

label: HCHLSS
comment: Finds a Host location access context and the related host and space and one related subnet.

label: Hc-pN-hP
comment: Finds a Host connected to but not providing an Abstract Subnet, which controlled by a Process not running on the Host.

label: HcWHS
comment: Finds a WiFiLAN hotspot and its local implementation in a Space, and a host connected to the hotspot in that space.

label: HHu2d
comment: Finds a host with two distinct interactive users.

label: H-iR-iMCHIUS
comment: Finds a Host that is not a Router or a Mobile Console Host in a Public Space connected to the Internet.

label: HL3S
comment: Finds a host connected to an L3 subnet, and an associated network access context, plus optionally the host manager.

label: HLnSP-hCLI
comment: Finds a Login Service and a Process used by it on the same Host that does not have a CLI.

label: HLS
comment: Finds a Host connected to a LogicalSubnet.

label: Hm2dHu
comment: Finds a host and two distinct humans that manage the host.

label: HmAC
comment: Finds a solo Host plus all location access contexts, and optionally the host manager and interactive user.

label: HP
comment: Finds a Process and its Host, and optionally the host manager and the interactive user of the process.

label: HPAC
comment: Finds a non-trivial Process running on a Host in a Space and the associated process access context, plus optionally the host manager, the interactive process user, and all related access contexts.

label: HPHLS-S
comment: Finds a logical subnet to which is connected a host that directly is or indirectly has a physical host, but the subnet is not accessible from any space where the host can be located. Note that there must be at least one host location, so this threat should not detect inferred routers implementing abstract subnets.

label: HP-iT
comment: Finds a non-trivial Process and its Host, and optionally the host manager and the interactive user of the process.

label: HPmAC
comment: Finds a Process and its Host with associated access contexts, and optionally the host manager and the interactive user of the process.

label: HprL3SAC
comment: Finds a Layer 3 LogicalSubnet provided by a Host, along with an associated network access context.

label: HprLS
comment: Finds a LogicalSubnet provided by a Host.

label: HprLSAC
comment: Finds a LogicalSubnet provided by a Host and an associated network access context.

label: HPS2AC
comment: Finds a non-trivial process running on a host in a space and the host location access context, with all related process access contexts, and optionally the host manager and process user.

label: HPS2NC
comment: Finds a process running on a host in a space and the host location access context, with all related process network access contexts.

label: HRASuSC
comment: Finds a Client using a Process via a Remote Access Service on the same Host.

label: HuCurHRASuP
comment: Finds a Human using a Remote Access Client to access a Process via a collocated Remote Access Service.

label: HuCurHRASuPurS
comment: Finds a Human using a Remote Access Client to access a Service via a Remote Access Service and collocated Process.

label: HuE
comment: Finds a human interacting with an email client.

label: HuHE
comment: Finds a human interacting directly with an email client running on a host.

label: HuHE2AC
comment: Finds a human interacting directly with an email client running on a host in a space, plus the associated location access context, and related process access contexts corresponding to the subnet connections of the host.

label: Hui2H
comment: Finds a physical Host with two distinct interactive users.

label: HuiCHLnS-AC
comment: Finds a human interacting with a console host and a login service running on a remote host, where the user does not interact with a terminal client that uses the login service.

label: HuiDH
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Dumb Host (which is not possible).

label: HuiHAC
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a host that runs an authentication client.

label: HuiH-Hu
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Host that has no manager.

label: HuiHoSt
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Host but not with any of its processes, and optionally their employer.

label: HuiHP
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process running on a Host.

label: HuiHP-m
comment: Finds a Human interacting with an unmanaged Process running on a Host.

label: HuiHPSP
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process running on an interactive Host located in a private space.

label: HuiHRAC
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a host that runs a remote access client.

label: HuiHS
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Host located in a space.

label: HuiHSt
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Host, and their employer.

label: HuimH-e
comment: Finds a human without access to email who is interacting with at least one console host.

label: HuiPCH
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process running on a fixed console host.

label: HuiPCHS
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process running on a fixed Host located in a space, plus associated process access contexts.

label: HuiPCHS-iP
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process running on a Host which is not their personal device, located in a space, plus associated process access contexts.

label: HuiPDaS-S
comment: Finds a Human that has access to a space and uses a Personal Device which has no specified location.

label: HuiPH-Hu
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Personal Host that has no manager.

label: HuiPH-iD
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Personal Host, where there is no self-referential link indicating that the device is shared with other users.

label: HuiPoSt
comment: Finds a Human using an interactive Process (but not a login shell), and an optional employer of the Human.

label: HuiPSt
comment: Finds a Human interacting directly with a Process, along with their employer and their contexts for accessing the Process.

label: HuirP
comment: Finds a Human remotely interacting with a Process.

label: HuirRACP
comment: Finds a Human interacting remotely with a Process via a Remote Access Clent which remotely uses the Process.

label: HumCH
comment: Finds a Human managing a Fixed Console Host.

label: HumCHS-iP
comment: Finds a Human managing a Host located in a space via the console, where the host is not a personal device.

label: HumH
comment: Finds a Human managing a Host.

label: HumHoSt
comment: Finds a Human managing a Host, and an optional employer of the Human.

label: HumHP
comment: Finds a Human managing a host running a process, and optionally an interactive process user.

label: HumHP-im
comment: Finds a Human managing a host running a process which has neither a manager nor an interactive user.

label: HumHP-iT
comment: Finds a Human managing a host running a non-trivial process, and optionally an interactive process user.

label: HumHSt
comment: Finds a Human managing a Host and their employer.

label: HumH-StSt
comment: Finds a Human who does not work for anyone else, managing a Host that has no operator.

label: HummH-e
comment: Finds a human without access to email who is managing at least one host, but not interacting with any host.

label: HumPH-m
comment: Finds an unmanaged host running a process that has a manager.

label: HumP-StSt
comment: Finds a Human managing a Process, where the Human is not an employee, and the Process has no operator.

label: HuoH-m
comment: Finds a Human operating an unmanaged Host.

label: HuPCH
comment: Finds a Human interacting with a Process that is not a Remote Access Service running on an Interactive Host.

label: HuSHPAC
comment: Finds a human interacting directly with a process from a space, and the associated context.

label: HuSP
comment: Finds a human user interacting with a smartphone which is a personal device with no other users.

label: HuwStmH-St
comment: Finds a Human working for an Employer, who manages a Host that has no other operator.

label: HuwStmP-St
comment: Finds a Human working for an Employer, and managing a Process that has no  operator.

label: IcP
comment: Finds a Process controlling an Internet class subnet.

label: InternetMP
comment: Finds an Internet class network.

label: IpH
comment: Finds a Host providing an Internet class subnet.

label: LnScPSHS2AC
comment: Finds a remote access service controlling a process running on a shell host in a space, and a location access context to the remote access service, related process access contexts and optionally the process manager.

label: LnScSHS2AC
comment: Finds a remote access service controlling a shell host in a space, and a location access context to the process, related host access contexts and optionally the host manager.

label: LnSucP
comment: Finds a remote access service using a back end process which controls access to the remote access service. This situation is a logical impossibility, as to use another service from a remote access service, the user must login to the remote access service.

label: LnSuP-H
comment: Finds a login service using a process where the two do not have the same Host.

label: LS
comment: Finds a solo Logical Subnet.

label: LS-iH
comment: Finds a solo Logical Subnet.

label: LS-prH
comment: Finds a Logical Subnet not provided by any host.

label: MHC
comment: Finds a solo Mobile Console Host.

label: MHcIS
comment: Finds a Mobile Console Host in a Public Space connected to the Internet.

label: MHHS
comment: Finds a Host whose physical host is a Mobile Console Host in a Space, where it can access at least one Logical Subnet (this pattern contains only multiple network access contexts), plus optionally an interactive user and system manager.

label: PccP
comment: Finds two processes, each of which controls the other. This is the simplest case of a cyclic authentication dependency, which is a logical impossibility.

label: PC-LnS
comment: Finds a physical Cluster that is not controlled by any process.

label: PCPHLSS
comment: Finds a Process location access context and the related process, host and space and one related subnet.

label: PcWH
comment: Finds a WiFiLAN and its local implementation, plus a controlling process.

label: PH
comment: Finds a solo physical host, and optionally its manager.

label: PH2
comment: Finds a process with two distinct hosts.

label: PHdH
comment: Finds a host that has a physical host (but is not the physical host).

label: PHHPS
comment: Finds a process running on a host that can be accessed from a space.

label: PHHS
comment: Finds a host that directly is or indirectly has a physical host in a space, and all connected logical subnets accessible from that space.

label: PHLSS
comment: Finds a host that has or directly is a physical host in a space and is connected to a logical subnet accessible from that space (other than an abstract hotspot).

label: PHS
comment: Finds a Physical Host located in a Space, and optionally the host manager and interactive user.

label: PH-S
comment: Finds a physical host that is not located in any space.

label: PHS2AC
comment: Finds a process running on a host in a space and an associated process location access context, plus related host access contexts and optionally the host manager and process user.

label: PHS2NC
comment: Finds a process running on a host in a space and an associated process location access context, plus related process network access contexts.

label: PHS-iC
comment: Finds a Physical Host that is not a Cluster located in a Space, and optionally the host manager and interactive user.

label: PMHHS
comment: Finds a non-trivial Process running on a host whose physical host is a Mobile Console Host that may be located in a Space, plus associated process network access contexts from that Space, and optionally an interactive Process user.

label: PnH
comment: Finds a Process with no Host.

label: PSHS2AC
comment: Finds a process running on a shell host in a space, and a location access context to the process, related host access contexts and optionally the host manager.

label: PS-iH
comment: Finds a solo Physical Subnet that is not a hotspot.

label: RAC
comment: Finds a remote access client.

label: RAS
comment: Finds a remote access service.

label: Rr
comment: Finds a solo Router.

label: Rr-LnS
comment: Finds a Router that is not controlled by any process.

label: RSSH
comment: Finds a Radio Subnet provided by a Gateway Host accessible from a Space, and optionally the service controlling access to it and the gateway manager.

label: RSS-HP
comment: Finds a Radio Subnet accessible from a Space, and the subnet it implements locally, where there is no gateway specified as the subnet provider and no controlling Process.

label: RSSH-P
comment: Finds a Radio Subnet with no controlling process, provided by a Gateway host and accessible from a Space, plus optionally the manager of the Gateway.

label: RTuRAS
comment: Finds a remote terminal client using a remote access service.

label: RTuRTuS-uR
comment: Finds a remote terminal using remotely another remote terminal which is using remotely a third process that is not yet remotely used by the first.

label: SH
comment: Finds a Shell Host (i.e. a host that allows user commands with the rights of the administrator or some user/process).

label: SHAC
comment: Finds a Shell Host plus optionally its manager, and an associated access context.

label: SHGP
comment: Finds a simple host running a general process.

label: SH-mHu
comment: Finds a Shell Host that has no manager.

label: SHP
comment: Finds a Process running on a shell Host, and optionally the interactive process user and host manager.

label: SHP-iT
comment: Finds a non-trivial Process running on a shell Host, and optionally the interactive process user and host manager.

label: SHPS2AC
comment: Finds a process running on a shell host in a space, and a location access context to the host, associated process access contexts and optionally the process user and host manager.

label: SHuPH-Hu
comment: Finds a Human managing a Space in which an unmanaged Fixed Host is located.

label: StDC
comment: Finds a stakeholder operating a data centre.

label: StH
comment: Finds a stakeholder operating a Host.

label: StHP
comment: Finds a Stakeholder operating a Host that runs a Process.

label: StSPH-St
comment: Finds a Private Space operated by a Stakeholder where a Fixed Host with no operator is located.

label: StS-St
comment: Finds a Private Space operated by a Stakeholder where access is not controlled by any stakeholder.

label: Sv-LnS
comment: Finds a Server that is not controlled by any process.

label: TH
comment: Finds a solo trivial host, and optionally the host manager, an interactive user, and any related access contexts.

label: THGP
comment: Finds a trivial host running a general process.

label: TP
comment: Finds a solo trivial process.

label: WHmWS
comment: Finds a WiFi hotspot with at least one local implementation.

label: WiFiSSoH
comment: Finds a WiFi subnet accessible from a Space, the network it implements, and optionally the host providing the subnet and service controlling access to it.

label: WmPH
comment: Finds a solo World asset (i.e. the inferred global public space), in which at least one Host is assumed to be (due to having no other defined location).

label: WpHS-aF
comment: Finds a mobile host or virtual host running on it, in a space, providing a WiFi LAN which is not accessible from any space, and providing no other WiFiLAN accessible in its space.

label: WpHSH-aF
comment: Finds a mobile host or virtual host running on it, in a space, providing a WiFi LAN which is a hotspot, and no other WiFiLAN accessible in its space.

label: WS-H
comment: Finds a solo WiFiLAN that is not an abstract hotspot.

label: WSSH
comment: Finds a Wired Subnet provided by a Gateway host accessible from a Space, and optionally the process controlling access and the manager of the gateway.

label: WSS-HP
comment: Finds a Wired Subnet accessible from a Space, where there is no gateway specified as the subnet provider, and no controlling Process.

label: WSSH-P
comment: Finds a Wired Subnet with no controlling process, provided by a Gateway host accessible from a Space, and optionally the manager of the Gateway.

label: GdHRS
comment: Finds a gateway providing a radio subnet to which a distinct host is connected, and optionally a process controlling access to the radio subnet, which in this case implements an abstract network (hotspot or cellular network), i.e. there is an implements relationship to a distinct abstract subnet.

label: GdHRSi
comment: Finds a gateway providing a radio subnet to which a distinct host is connected, and optionally a process controlling access to the radio subnet, which in this case does not implement a separate abstract network (hotspot or cellular network), i.e. it has a self-referential implements relationship.

label: GdHWS
comment: Finds a gateway providing a wired subnet to which a distinct host is connected, and optionally a process controlling access to the subnet.

label: HIoH
comment: Finds a Host connected to the Internet, and the associated network Interface, plus optionally the host manager.

label: HLoH
comment: Finds a Host with optional system manager, connected to a Layer 2 Logical Subnet, and the associated network Interface, and a second, distinct host on the same subnet.

label: HRoH
comment: Finds a Host with optional system manager, connected to a Layer 3 Logical Subnet (but not the Internet), and the associated network Interface, and a second, remote host on the same subnet.

label: HRSGSoS
comment: Finds a host connecting to a radio subnet that is not an abstract hotspot, a gateway host located in a space that is providing the radio subnet, and optionally a service that controls access to the radio subnet.

label: HSRSoGS
comment: Finds a host located in a space connecting to a radio subnet that is not a hotspot, plus optionally the controlling host and service for the subnet.

label: HSWSoGS
comment: Finds a host located in a space connecting to a wired subnet it does not provide, plus optionally the host manager, and the gateway and service controlling the subnet.

label: HWSGSoS
comment: Finds a host connecting to a wired network it does not provide, a gateway host located in a space that is providing the network, and optionally the gateway host manager, and a service that controls access to the network.

label: I
comment: Finds a solo Interface, plus the associated host and subnet (which is not a hotspot) and optionally the host manager.

label: I3c-rGrL3
comment: Finds a Gateway host that is not a Mobile Client connected from the Internet to a distinct IP subnet, both in the same space.

label: I3c-rMrL3
comment: Finds a Mobile Client host connected from the Internet to a distinct IP subnet, both in the same space.

label: ILSA
comment: Finds an Interface connecting to a Logical Subnet that implements an Abstract Subnet that is not the same as the Logical Subnet.

label: INC
comment: Finds a solo Interface, plus the associated host, subnet, and a host network access context where the interface is connected.

label: IoH
comment: Finds an open network path from the Internet to (but not via) a Host connected to a local subnet, and the associated network interface and access context, plus the location contexts for the host being on that subnet, and optionally the host manager.

label: L3-Ic-rGcL3
comment: Finds a Gateway host connected from an IP subnet (not the Internet) that it does not provide to a distinct IP subnet, both in the same space.

label: L3rGc-rL3
comment: Finds a Host connected from an IP subnet to a distinct IP subnet, the former but not the latter being provided by the Host, and both in the same space.

label: L3rGrL3
comment: Finds a Host providing two distinct IP subnets both in the same space.

label: L3SSg2
comment: Finds a gateway from an IP subnet to a distinct IP subnet, along with the forward and (open) return path segments via the gateway.

label: L3SSg2AC
comment: Finds a gateway from an IP subnet to a distinct IP subnet, along with the forward and (open) return path segments via the gateway, and a context in which the gateway is connected to both subnets.

label: LoH
comment: Finds a Host in a context where it is connected to a Layer 2 Logical Subnet, and the associated network interface, plus all contexts where it is connected to the same subnet (there may be others), and optionally the host manager.

label: LPCSg
comment: Finds a logical path traversing a closed segment.

label: LPLS2NSg2
comment: Finds a route between subnets through a gateway where NAT is used on the return path, and a logical path traversing the forward segment.

label: LPsLS
comment: Finds a Logical Subnet at the start of a Logical Path.

label: LS2NSg2
comment: Finds a route between subnets through a gateway where NAT is used on the return path, and optionally the gateway manager.

label: LS2NSg2AC
comment: Finds a route between subnets through a gateway where NAT is used on the return path, plus a context in which the gateway is connected to both subnets, and optionally the gateway manager.

label: LS2RSg2
comment: Finds a route between subnets through a gateway where NAT is not used on the return path, and optionally the gateway device manager.

label: NoH
comment: Finds an open network path not via the Internet from a remote attacker subnet to (but not via) a Host connected to a local subnet, and the associated network interface and access context, plus the location contexts for the host being on that subnet, and optionally the host manager.

label: NPLS
comment: Finds a Network Path that starts and ends on the same subnet, i.e. it uses no gateways.

label: NPmLSmSg
comment: Finds a Network Path that traverses at least one Logical Segment, plus the Logical Subnet(s) it visits (in this pattern there should be more than one).

label: RoH
comment: Finds an open network path from a remote attacker L3 subnet to (and not via) a Host in a space connected to a local subnet, and the associated network interface, plus the contexts in which the host is so connected (there must be at least one), and optionally the host manager.

label: RScGcRS
comment: Finds a Physical Host connected between two distinct WiFi subnets, both in the same space.

label: Sg
comment: Finds a gateway host between two subnets, plus the logical segments representing routes between the subnets via this gateway.

label: SgHfILS
comment: Finds a Logical Segment via a Host routing from a Logical Subnet, and the Interface between the Host and Logical Subnet.

label: SgHtILS
comment: Finds a Logical Segment via a Host routing to a Logical Subnet, and the Interface between the Host and Logical Subnet.

label: WScMcWS
comment: Finds a Mobile Host connected between two distinct Wired LANs, both in the same space.

label: NP2LS
comment: Finds a network path with a subpath that visits a subnet.

label: NP2LSg
comment: Finds a network path with a subpath that traverses a logical segment.

label: NP3
comment: Finds a Network Path with a subpath that extends a third path, which does not itself have a subpath relationship to the first.

label: OPLS1
comment: Finds a zero-length Logical Path and a Path Terminator (NPE) to a Logical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route via a Gateway Host to the Subnet from some other Logical Subnet.

label: OPLS2
comment: Finds a Network Path and terminator (NPE) to a destination Logical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route into the Subnet at the start of the Path via a Gateway, from a Subnet not visited by any shorter path to the destination, where the Path is routed via at least one Host but not via the Gateway.

label: OPPS1
comment: Finds a zero-length Physical Path and a Path Terminator (PPE) to a Physical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route via a Physical Gateway Host to the Subnet from some other Physical Subnet.

label: OPPS2
comment: Finds a Physical Path and terminator (PPE) to a destination Physical Subnet, where there is a Logical Route into the Subnet at the start of the Path via a Gateway, from a Physical Subnet not visited by any shorter physical path to the destination, where the Path is routed via at least one Host but not via the Gateway.

label: HPAC-AC
comment: Finds a Process running on a Host in a Space and the associated process access context, where the process does not run in any access context.

label: HuaSaE
comment: Finds a human with access to a space that is accessible from a public entrance space.

label: HuPSoSt
comment: Finds a Human with access to a Private Space, and an optional employer of the Human.

label: HuPSSt
comment: Finds a Human with access to a Private Space, and their employer.

label: PPS
comment: Finds a Private Physical Space.

label: PPS-E
comment: Finds a Private Space that is not accessible from any other Space.

label: PScSt
comment: Finds a private space controlled by a stakeholder.

label: PSS
comment: Finds two spaces, one of which is private and accessible via the other.

label: DHuDC
comment: Finds a data asset relating to a human along with a stored copy of the data.

label: DHuDF
comment: Finds a data asset relating to a human along with a flowing copy of the data.
